		<description><![CDATA[My team recently worked with Happy Cog who uses Macaw, and they turned us onto the idea of prototyping. So I&#039;ve been trying out a few tools. I used Flash years ago and while being more visually-oriented, I found Actionscript a little painful. So my goal is to find an intuitive program with a friendly interactions interface that requires little to no coding:

1. Macaw - I found it good for creating simple responsive mocks, but there are little to no animation options. It was also buggy since it&#039;s a relatively new release. A few tutorials for basic clicks and transitions, but very few complex interaction examples.
2. Webflow - Definitely a step-up in animation options, but there&#039;s a bit of a learning curve.
3. Axure - The interface felt a little dated and I just didn&#039;t click wit